The Mexican Institute for Social Security (IMSS) announced that it was conducting an investigation to discover the gene of obesity in children and young people, known as the protocol 'Genetics of obesity in children and adolescents', which would allow to count with markers associated with obesity.
In a communication, the head of the Biochemical Medical Research Unit of the Hospital of Specialities of the National Medical Centre of the 21st Century Miguel Cruz López explained that a multidisciplinary team of doctors, nurses, nutritionists and social workers had been integrated.
This team is supported by postgraduate specialists from the National Institute of Public Health (INSP) and the Centre for Advanced Research and Studies (Cinvestäst) of the National Political Institute (NIP).
