Once the goal of meeting 500 or 600 minors is met, the study will continue in the Unit of Independent Sport (South of the Federal District) and finally in the Unit of Sport Morelos (north of the Federal District).
He explained that the purpose of this research was to know the components and importance of genetics with regard to the development of obesity and to identify risk factors in children and young Mexicans to prevent the occurrence of degenerative chronic diseases.
At the World Diabetes Day on 14 November, the goal was to gather 3,000 children and young people between six and 14 years of age, with the consent and supervision of their parents, for the implementation of specific food issues.
They will also be asked about the physical activity and previous legacy of diseases, with the aim of avoiding risk factors that trigger diseases such as diabetes or renal failure.
The Saturdays were applied to all participants in anthropometric measurements (weight, size, circumference of the belt), blood pressure taking, determination of glucose levels, triglycerides, cholesterol and insulin and genetics (to identify genes associated with child obesity).
Cruz López noted that this research is subject to the concern of health professionals about alarming weight gain in children.
" Health surveys in 1999 and 2006 indicated that there had been an increase of 77 per cent in obesity in children within just six years, and 47 per cent in girls; there was also a dramatic rise in terms of obesity," IMSS expert noted.
He indicated that the justification for the search for markers was supported in that the country's population differed from others by its genetic history.
He reported that, on average, Mexico has 65 per cent of American Indian heritage, 30 per cent of European and 5 per cent of Africans and this condition is reflected in the genes associated with diabetes and overweight.
He explained that generally obesity genetics are translated into the inability to burn the excess energy we consume (calories) and stored in fat.
The researcher explained that the direct benefit for participants is the comprehensive evaluation of children, which allows them to detect if they are in some degree overweight or obesity.
In fact, he said, the presence of dark-colored (ancantosis) patches in the neck and front, indicating the likelihood of metabolic changes and even prediabetes.
The information is managed confidentially, the doctors provide it in writing to parents, who are told about each of the measurements and changes in life-style that they must make in order to prevent diseases.
Cruz López explained that there are three main components that cause obesity, obesity and other chronic disorders: sedentaryism, which is the lack of daily physical activity, to stay most of the day sitting in front of the television and to use means of transport instead of walking short distances.
It is also due to the high caloric intake, i.e. the highest consumption of acidic beverages, carbohydrates (tamales, bread, pizza, hamburgese, etc.) with high levels of fats and proteins and genetics analysed in this protocol.
