Later, Gazprom rented to that company, for a period of twenty-five years renewables, the total capacity of gas transport.
"Gazprom will pay for its total capacity, regardless of the amount of gas actually transported," says Jens Müller.
The financing of the construction of the pipeline has been completed by 30 per cent with the contribution of shareholders and by 70 per cent through bank loans.
The total cost of work should amount to EUR 7,400 million for both tubes.
For GDF Suez, for example, investment has reached 240 million.
But minority shareholders are confident that they will not exceed their investment, since Gazprom assumes only the risk of spending.
